INTERSHOP IOM 4.8.0-SNAPSHOT Database Model   (revision 8ee926f81393b5181cac82e4a3ea2871a732af9a)

Enumeration Tables

These tables have equivalent JAVA Enum Classes and their content should never be modified by hand.

Schema Table Rows Comment
oms  ApprovalStateCodeDefDO  5  Approval response state codes that are supported from the application by default. 
oms  ApprovalStateCodeReasonDefDO  12  Approval state code reasons that are supported from the application by default.

oms  CommunicationVersionBeanNameDefDO  2  Communication beans versions that are supported by the application.
Currently only the 'CommunicationInBeanManagerBean' is referenced. 
oms  CommunicationVersionDefDO  2  Relations between a API-versions and specific versions of communication beans. The initial relations are supported from the application by default
A relation can be noted as a mapping of versions.
Currently only "v1.0" is supported. 
oms  CountryCodeDefDO  7  Country codes, e.g. "ISO3166 ALPHA-2 Code". 
oms  CountryDefDO  244  Countries that are supported by the platform by default. The related currency and iso-codes are included. 
oms  DecisionBeanDefDO  20  Decision beans that are supported by the application by default.
A decision bean is an implementation that checks whether a following action should be processes or not, for example the check whether an e-mail should be send or not. 
oms  DeliveryFormDefDO  3  Delivery forms that are supported from the platform by default, e.g. "Standard". 
oms  DeliveryOptionDefDO  9  Delivery options that are supported from the platform by default, e.g. "Cash on delivery".
An order position can have more than one option. 
oms  DeliveryTypeDefDO  2  Delivery types describe expected delivery times. The types EARLIEST and FIXED are not listed here as they depend on a date. 
oms  DocumentFormatDefDO  8  Document formats including related encodings, mime-types and transformer factories.

Document formats are for example pdf, xml.
Document encodings are for example utf-8.
Transformer factories are used to transform data and/ or templates to a final document. E.g. to a pdf.
Mime-types are for example "application/pdf", "application/xml". 
oms  EventDefDO  4  Business event listener types.
Supported business events are for example related to customer e-mails, payment actions and invoicing 
oms  ExecutionBeanDefDO  22  Execution bean are single executable java beans that can be called inside business processes to handle specific tasks.
Such tasks are for example the creation of documents, the import of products and more. 
oms  ExecutionBeanKeyDefDO  120  Execution bean keys are additional configurable properties that are used from {@link ExecutionBeanDefDO}.
Customer e-mails for example use at least the property keys "shopEmailAddress" and "messageTemplate" (ExecutionBeanDefDO is SHOP_CUSTOMER_MAIL_SENDER). 
oms  FileTransferJobTypeDefDO  3  Configuration Object for the different file transfer types (e.g. push or pull) 
oms  IdentCodeGenerationBeanDefDO  3  Supported Ident code generators.
Ident codes in general are used from carriers. 
oms  InvoicingEventDefDO  1  Supported invoice event handlers.
Currently only the creation of an invoice is supported. 
oms  InvoicingTypeDefDO  2  Types of invoices that are supported from the platform by default, e.g. "invoice". 
oms  JobDefDO  15  Jobs that are supported from the application by default. These jobs are based on the application job framework.
A job can be attached to a schedule that will execute it.
Note that the job framework is based on a single quartz job of the application server but has no further relations to the other offered quartz jobs. 
oms  MailEventDefDO  1  Supported customer e-mail event handlers.
Currently only the sending of a customer e-mail is supported. 
oms  MergeTypeDefDO  2  Merge types that are supported from the platform by default, e.g. "MERGE_MASTER". 
oms  MessageTypeDefDO  133  Message types of the order-log.
Message types are for example "Send order message", "Received release message". 
oms  NumberRangeFormatterDefDO  1  Business Object to define number range calculation methods (e.g. for invoice numbers) 
oms  ObjectTypeDefDO  36  Supported business objects types.
Types are for example orders, responses, transmissions. 
oms  OrderOptimizeDefDO  2  Order optimization types that are supported from the application by default, e.g. optimization by price. 
oms  OrderPosStatesDefDO  42  Supported Order position states.
Order positions states representing the current state of processing an order position.
States are for example INITIAL, ANNOUNCED, DISPATCHED. 
oms  OrderStatesDefDO  43  Supported Order states.
Order states representing the current state of processing an order.
States are for example INITIAL, ANNOUNCED, DISPATCHED.
